    <Ritual>
        <Nerangs id="ritualNerangs">
            <ab>Y63.7 (mss. 6, 40, 400, 410):</ab>
            <ab class="ab_indent">
                <em>yeŋ́hē hātąm</em> tā gyāg pad mayānag ī barsom sar pad war ī zōhrag</ab>
            <ab class="ab_indent">
                "At <em>yeŋ́hē hātąm</em> until the end, he puts (the <em>hāwan</em>) in the middle of the <em>barsom</em>, next to the <em>zōhrag</em>."</ab>
        </Nerangs>
        <Quotations id="ritualQuotations">
    <ab>Cf. N52.8 (cf. <bibl>Kotwal and Kreyenbroek, 2003</bibl>)</ab>
    <ab class="ab_indent">
                <em>vīspaēibiiō ẏasnō.kərətaēibiiō maδəmāi *barəsmąn
paiti.barōit̰</em>
            </ab>
<ab class="ab_indent">During all recitations of the Yeŋhehātā, he should bring ()the offering) to the middle part of the <em>barəsman</em>
            </ab>
        </Quotations>
    </Ritual>

